div.p:
I find this part even deeper, if that is possible, than the first; in it you say very much that is true, which people here in Holland do need to hear. I sent one painting to the annual [exhibition] at Arnhem, which was rejected;
			            to Brussels four of the most recent: the “Mill”, the Woods, a Flower and the May morning you mentioned, describing it so beautifully, and everything was accepted there – and, so I have heard, appreciated by various painters.
			            In your appreciation, I have here experienced the kind of appreciation shown Teirlinck. So we do have such a man of letters, too. But the painters: they are different there.
